item.description:
Recently I have been writing a WebApi project which needs to accept plaintext via the body of a PUT request, and did the logical thing of using the FromBodyAttribute
public HttpStatusCode PutKv([FromBody]string content, string keyGreedy) { return HttpStatusCode.OK; } Which didn&rsquo;t work, with the useful error message of &ldquo;Unsupported media type.&rdquo;
It turns out that to bind a value type with the FromBody attribute, you have to prefix the body of your request with an =.
